# first-boot-deferred.list — packages installed on first boot, NOT on the base ISO
# Author: RKOJ-ELENO :: 2026-05-24
#
# Format: one row per package, "<repo>:<pkg>".
#   repo = pacman  -> sudo pacman -S --noconfirm --needed <pkg>
#   repo = aur     -> yay -S --noconfirm --needed <pkg>   (yay bootstrapped by sinister-first-boot-install-yay.sh)
# Lines starting with # are comments. Blank lines ignored.
#
# Source: packages.x86_64.removed Categories 12 (deferred comms/media) +
# 13 (AUR-only operator-pinned tools). 17 rows total, matching the
# PACKAGE-AUDIT-2026-05-24.md FIRST-BOOT-DEFERRED set.

# --- Category 12: comms + media (heavy multilib pulls — defer for ISO size) ---
pacman:discord
pacman:obs-studio
pacman:spotify-launcher
pacman:lutris

# --- Category 13: AUR-only operator-pinned tools (yay required) ---
aur:zen-browser-bin
aur:rustdesk-bin
aur:tresorit-cli
aur:proton-ge-custom
aur:obsidian
aur:openrgb

# --- VM / containers (operator runs Docker Desktop on Windows + occasional VMs) ---
pacman:qemu-desktop
pacman:virt-manager
pacman:libvirt
pacman:edk2-ovmf
pacman:docker
pacman:docker-compose

# --- Phone / android tooling (operator has platform-tools for QPilotos work) ---
pacman:android-tools
